# Rule: Hybrid Feature Architecture Boundaries

## Core Principle

Use feature-first colocation by default, with strict centralization for truly shared or global concerns.

## Feature Module Boundaries

- Keep single-use APIs, feature-local state, feature components, and feature-specific types inside `src/features/<feature-name>/`.
- Treat each feature as an encapsulated module.
- Do not deep-import internals from one feature into another feature.

## Shared/Core Promotion Rules

- Promote code to `src/shared/` or `src/core/` only when it is used by multiple features.
- Keep common UI primitives (including shared Shadcn wrappers), global hooks, and generic utilities in shared/core.
- If a feature-local component/function is needed by a second feature, move it to shared/core first, then import from that centralized location.

## Example Decisions

- If `src/features/orders/components/OrderBadge` is needed by `billing`, promote it to `src/shared/components/OrderBadge` before reuse.
- If `src/features/checkout/api/createCheckoutSession` is only used in checkout, keep it under checkout.
